entries.meaning: (computing, telegraphy) An input device whose few keys can be pressed in many combinations, often simultaneously, to enter different commands or characters.
(computing, databases) A set of keys (unique identifiers) used to distinguish the rows of data being traversed by a cursor.
(rare) A collection of keys on a typewriter or keyboard.
examples: This typewriter has a numeric keyset to the right of the standard alphanumeric keyset.
